properties.areaDesc: Upper Columbia Basin; Moses Lake Area
properties.headline: Wind Advisory issued January 31 at 2:18PM PST until February 1 at 6:00PM PST by NWS Spokane WA
properties.description:
...THE HIGH WIND WATCH IS NO LONGER IN EFFECT...

* WHAT...Southwest winds 25 to 35 mph with gusts up to 50 mph
expected.

* WHERE...Moses Lake Area and Upper Columbia Basin.

* WHEN...From 6 AM to 6 PM PST Saturday.

* IMPACTS...Gusty winds could blow around unsecured objects.
Tree limbs could be blown down and a few power outages may
result.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Strongest winds will occur east of
Ritzville and Wilbur over the rising terrain of the eastern
Columbia Basin.
properties.instruction:
Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high
profile vehicle. Secure outdoor objects.

NWSheadline: WIND ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 6 AM TO 6 PM PST SATURDAY
